The paper deals with computational complexity and graph theory, which are both covered by cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the properties of graphs, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves optimization problems, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Game Theory).
